 was giving a speech in Trenton, New Jersey this morning, and he basically said that if the Senate changed the &quot;Homeland Security Bill&quot; in anyway that took away from the President having complete and unaccountable control of the military in times of crisis he would veto it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udiekan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Diekan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 10:35:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=989.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bush's Speech this morning.</span><hr size=1> Thank God for checks and balance. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utrindle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trindle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1011<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 10:42:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=989.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bush's Speech this morning.</span><hr size=1> Actually I believe the issues in question concern the collective bargaining rights and civil service protections of 170,000 federal employees who would be transferred to fall under the Dept. of Homeland Security. Let's not forget that he made these comments at a Republican fundraiser which US tax payers will have to pick up the tab for. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukuwenfallenleaf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KuwenFallenleaf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.student.nada.kth.se/~md96-jma/eq/us.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Peanut Gallery</span><br>  Posts: 3014<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 10:57:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=989.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.interplay.com/bgate2/images2/mainimage1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bush's Speech this morning.</span><hr size=1> uuuuh ok, I don't think the GOP fund raisers use tax payer money. Money they have raised in the past maybe which is no where near what they would raise at one of these events. Dems do the same thing...if they have money in their own party coffers they will organize an event to raise more. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umuglackdackfut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Muglack DackFut</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of Mulletude</span><br>  Posts: 2652<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 11:03:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=989.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bush's Speech this morning.</span><hr size=1> Actually no Trindle, you're 100% wrong. He said that the President needs complete control of the military, because terrorists act quickly, and so going through normal processes wouldn't be fast enough. He then said a bunch of shit about this not being a Republican or Democrat thing, as people from both camps are on both sides of the fence. He then stated that if Senate modified the bill so that the President wouldn't have complete control and unquestionable control in times of crisis he would Veto his own bill. His reasons had nothing to do with moving people or any of that. He basically said &quot;all or none&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utrindle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trindle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1012<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 11:51:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=989.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bush's Speech this morning.</span><hr size=1> What in hell are you talking about Muglack? The central issue of debate between the two versions of the Homeland Security bill is over the dropping of civil service protections and collective bargaining rights of federal employees. 50,000 of the employees set to be transferred to the new department are already in unions and the rest are covered under civil service laws. President Bush wants to gain the authority to shut down unions and suspend the rights aforementioned as he sees fit &quot;in the interests of national security&quot; which would follow a long standing trend of union busting. <br>
<br>
Bush drew a line in the sand and has threatened to veto a bill that doesn't provide him with these powers. THAT is where the debate is occurring over the two bills and is where his comments are originating from. The Homeland Security bill has nothing to do with the armed forces Muglack.<br>
<br>
Please provide a link to your source since it is totally at odds with every other news source I have found on his recent speech in Trenton. I'll be happy to read it once provided and respond. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tuggan>Tuggan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 12:06:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=989.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bush's Speech this morning.</span><hr size=1> You must give in to the Master of Mulletude, Trindle.  Hes always right.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umuglackdackfut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Muglack DackFut</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of Mulletude</span><br>  Posts: 2654<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 12:30:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=989.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bush's Speech this morning.</span><hr size=1> I don't know past debates, and I don't know what the source of conflict is on in the senate. I do know I was an hour late for work this morning because I stayed at home to watch what he had to say. I do know he said that Terrorists act to quickly for a government to respond in the normal way, and if the office of the President isn't given the ability to respond immediatly then there's no point in even bothering with the bill and he would veto it.<br>
<br>
Maybe the workers is the main issue for debate in the Senate but Bush said that if the bill is changed so that the Office of the President isn't allowed to act without an ok from the Senate or Congress (the way he made it sound only the Senate had issue with it) then the entire purpose iof the proposed bill was lost and it would not go through. Then he made his standard &quot;this is a bi-partisan thing&quot; and the crap he always talks about because he is the &quot;Bi-Partisan President&quot;, and then moved on to discussing Education.<br>
<br>
So to re-itterate, in the speech this morning Bush said that if the president isn't given the ability to act when the country is under threat then he will veto it. What the Senate is debating over, and what they may or may not agree with in the bill is a moot point. I merely passed on what I heard Bush say this morning in his speech.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utrindle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trindle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1013<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 12:35:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=989.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bush's Speech this morning.</span><hr size=1> You sure showed me Tuggan. When someone responds by saying you're 100% wrong, they should be prepared to defend their reasoning and expect a rebuttal. I responded with an opinion formed after consulting multiple news sources describing Bush's speech along with knowledge about the Homeland Security debate as well. The sources I researched seem at odds with Muglack's comments and I rightly asked him for a link to what he read to see if there are differences before debating further. This is respect for his viewpoint and has nothing to do with some perceived superiority complex. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umuglackdackfut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Muglack DackFut</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of Mulletude</span><br>  Posts: 2657<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 12:57:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=989.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bush's Speech this morning.</span><hr size=1> Tuggan was trying to be funny, and I believe his post was a poor attempt at sarcasm. As I said, I don't what the ongoing debate concerns, and I don't know what the Senate's major issue is, and I wasn't making any mention of that. All I was saying is that in Bush's speech this morning (and I didn't read it anywhere, I heard him say it) he said that if the President wasn't given complete control of the military in times of need to act as he saw fit then he would veto it, because it wouldn't be effective any other way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=989.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=989.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=989.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=989.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.threadControl?topicID=989.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=989.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernfrm20.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=989.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<